description:
Cross-file interaction bug: lichen_l2_iface_init() sets lichen_iface before all initialization completes, preventing recovery.

lichen_l2.c:1596-1601:
  if (lichen_iface != NULL) {
    LOG_ERR('...init requires reboot after failure');
    atomic_set(&iface_init_failed, 1);
    return;
  }
  lichen_iface = iface;

lichen_l2.c:1604-1608 (after setting lichen_iface):
  ret = lichen_lora_l2_set_rx_callback(...);
  if (ret != 0) {
    atomic_set(&iface_init_failed, 1);
    return;
  }

SCENARIO:
1. First boot, lichen_lora_l2_init() succeeds (line 1473)
2. get_eui64() succeeds, memcpy succeeds
3. net_if_set_link_addr() succeeds
4. link_ctx initialized
5. lichen_iface set at line 1601
6. lichen_lora_l2_set_rx_callback() FAILS (e.g., lora module suddenly in UNINIT state due to bug)
7. iface_init_failed set, return
8. System tries to recover by calling init again somehow
9. Line 1596 check fails because lichen_iface is already set
10. No recovery possible without reboot

This is DOCUMENTED and INTENTIONAL (line 1597 message says 'requires reboot').

However, the write-once invariant for lichen_iface (project-LICHEN-ybal.4) is violated if init can fail AFTER setting lichen_iface. The invariant says 'set exactly once... never cleared' but init can fail after setting it.

FIX: Move lichen_iface assignment to AFTER all init checks succeed, just before atomic_set(&link_ctx_initialized, 1).
